\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Pour 1 1/2 cups pomegranate juice into an ice {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cube/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cube}} tray and freeze overnight.\
In a large bowl, mix the remaining 4 cups pomegranate juice, the pineapple juice, ginger ale, seltzer and pisco. Add the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/pomegranate/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 pomegranate}} ice cubes and serve in your favorite {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/punch/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 punch}} bowl.\
What Makes This Recipe Really Sing: Don't you just love when you go to a party and there is a specialty {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cocktail/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cocktail}}? (For some reason it always makes me happy.) This makes enough for a large crowd, this way everyone gets one or two and you don't have to work during the party. Pisco trivia also makes for great "Did ya know ...." conversation starters.\
BYOC: Feel free to throw in some pomegranate seeds on top. They will look like little jewels floating in your punch bowl. If you don't have a punch bowl and are serving this out of a pitcher you can {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garnish/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 garnish}} your glasses with pineapple slices. If you can't find pisco you can always use light {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/rum/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 rum}}\cf2 .}